  "original_title": "Ministry clarifies on public sector retirement age",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Ministry clarifies on public sector retirement age",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "COLOMBO (News 1st); The Ministry of Public Administration, Home Affairs, Provincial Councils, and Local Government says the decision to lower the retirement age to 60 years will NOT apply to selected essential professions.",
        "Ministry Secretary, M.M.P.K. Mayadunne says the 60-year retirement age will NOT apply to professions such as medicine, nursing, and engineering.",
        "He said new amendments will be presented to the Cabinet to raise the retirement age of such professions to 63 years.",
        "He said that for other sectors in the Public Service, all those over the age of 60 years will be sent on retirement with effect from the 31st of December 2022, and the respective circular will be issued within two weeks.",
        "Accordingly, over 20,000 employees in Public Services will be sent on retirement by the end of 2022.",
        "The Interim Budget by President Ranil Wickremesinghe proposed to reduce the retirement age of public sector and semi-governmental employees to 60 years.",
        "Earlier, the government decided to raise the mandatory retirement age of public sector employees to 65 years and that of semi-governmental employees to 62 years.",
        "Those who have been employed beyond 60 years of age at present in the government and semi-government sectors will be retired as of 31.12.2022.",
        "Promptly Resolve Fuel, Gas and Paddy Issues \u2013 Senior Advisor to the President"
      ],
